===Etymology===
{{ME.}} [[virtu]], from {{fro}}, from {{L.}} [[virtus]], ''manliness'', from [[vir]], ''man''. [[Category:Indo-European root *wī-ro-]]

===Noun===
'''virtue'''
# excellence in morals
# a good model quality
# chastity and faithfullness
# an exemplary (very good) quality 
# (''Biblical tradition'')  in Christian [[angelology]], the second level of [[angel]]s, ranked above [[angel]]s and below [[archangel]]s

